I am documenting my completion of the [30 Day SOC Challenge](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W3ExS2m6B24&list=PLG6KGSNK4PuBb0OjyDIdACZnb8AoNBeq6) posted by the [MyDFIR](http://www.youtube.com/@MyDFIR) YouTube Channel. The challenge was created to provide relevant experience to individuals seeking to obtain a SOC Analyst role. I will do my best to document the steps I took throughout. I am going to break the challenge up into parts. All of the servers were created in Vultr Cloud Platform.

The network diagram shows all of the servers that will be created, their function and location. 

To begin, I created a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) by navgiating to Products, clicking on Metwork dropdown and selecting VPC 2.0. Click on the blue Add VPC 2.0 Network.

